  "reveal": {
    "brief_voiced": "Nan Pringle stands as the killer. The Colonel's protocol demands every place laid with a loaded pistol save those beside ladies; Nan Pringle herself occupied the fifth place upon the host's left, and by that rule Captain Wat Frew's place at the sixth should have been unloaded. Yet the pistol at his place was found charged. She sat within reach of that deviation, the length of the left side clear between them, and the geometry offered means and opportunity both.\n\nNan Pringle pours the tea and keeps the accounts—she misses nothing, least of all the Captain's elastic accounting. He owed money by half the company, debts that touch even a poor relation tasked with the ledgers. The records would show what he owed, and to whom. A woman who knows every secret of a house, who sees what others do not, who tends its books and its trust, sees also when that trust is broken.\n\nThe file closes with a quiet turn of the page.",
